  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this observational study is to establish estimation of global lordosis of the
      cervical spine (from C3 to C7) in patients with cervicobrachial neuralgia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The main judgement critearia is the estimation in degree of this lordosis measured on EOS
      radiographies, The study includes adults patients with non traumatic cervicobrachial
      neuralgia caused by discal hernia free from any previous spine surgery.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
